          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The UAE has been officially named the safest country in the world in <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-25-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-numbeo-s-2025-mid-year-safety-index?source=website" target="_blank">Numbeo’s 2025 mid‑year Safety Index</a>, scoring 85.2 points. Andorra, Qatar, Taiwan, and Macao (China) followed in the top five.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
           Numbeo’s Safety Index is built from many crowd‑sourced surveys worldwide. It measures people’s sense of safety when walking alone during daylight and at night, as well as levels of crime, including theft, assault, and vandalism (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #102341; color: black;" href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-25-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-methodology?source=website" target="_blank">methodology</a>). A higher rating indicates a lower perceived crime percentage and a stronger sense of security.
          </p>
